                        Hi Mark! <br><br> We noticed a potential issue with your Fitbit watch. It looks like it might not be collecting heart rate. This is a common problem. We have outlined how to fix it below. Please call us if you have any issues. <b> Study Coordinator at coordinator_number.</b> or <b> Jon Clutton at 913-945-7683.</b> <br> <br>
                      </td>

                  <tr>
                    <td align="left">
                      <p style= "font-size:100%;"> 1) Take your watch off and see if there is a blinking green light. If not, continue to step 2. If there is a green light, call Jon Clutton. <br>
                                                   2) Open up your watch screen and scroll down (drag your finger down) and press SETTINGS.<br>
                                                   3) Scroll down to HEART RATE. If the bar is grey and to the left, continue to step 4. If the bar is blue and to the right, call Jon Clutton. <br>
                                                   4) Press Heart RATE and you should see the bar move to the right and turn blue. <br>
                                                   5) Take your watch off again and check for the blinking green light. It should be there now. If so, problem solved! Nicely done!<br><br></p>
                    </td>
                   </tr>
